Finance Minister Noda to Face Kaieda in Runoff Vote for Japan Leadership

-- B y   K y u n g   B o k   C h o
-- 
2011-08-29T04:34:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/finance-minister-noda-to-face-kaieda-in-runoff-vote-for-japan-leadership.html
Japanese Trade Minister  Banri Kaieda 
and Finance Minister  Yoshihiko Noda  advanced to the next round
of voting in the  Democratic Party  of  Japan ’s election for a new
leader today. Neither candidate succeeded in getting a majority
in the first round.  The winner of the runoff will succeed Prime Minister  Naoto
Kan , who announced on Aug. 26 he will resign. The president of
the Democratic Party becomes the nation’s premier because of its
strength in parliament.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyung Bok Cho at 
 kcho7@bloomberg.net  